('FLReq-996804', 'Displaying Real-Time Information on the Instrument Cluster', 'Displaying Real-Time Information on the Instrument Cluster
Preconditions:
The vehicle is powered on and in operational condition.
The Instrument Cluster (IC) is functional and capable of displaying real-time information. The IC is communicating with various sensors within the vehicle that provide real-time data (e.g., PRND, speed, battery levels, warnings, etc.). Main Scenario:
The user starts the vehicle. The sensors within the vehicle start sending real-time data to the Instrument Cluster. The IC displays essential real-time information, such as current speed, PRND state, battery levels, odometer readings, and relevant warning notifications. The user operates the vehicle while the IC continues to update and display the real-time data. As the driving conditions change (acceleration, deceleration, turning, etc.), the IC dynamically updates the displayed information accordingly. Post-condition:
The Instrument Cluster continuously displays and updates real-time information as the user operates the vehicle. ', 'IAT In progress', 0, 'PF-0147'),
