('I-7207', 'APS Main Scenario', 'Use Case: "APS Main Scenario"

Preconditions:

Context of use: Description of normal operation of the system when the driver interacts with it.
Goal: compensate insufficient driving skills and reduce maneuvering time
Main character: driver.
Target: parking lot lane marking, vehicle.

1. The system is turned on;
2. The car is moving along the road at a speed of up to 20 km/h;
3. The system detected a suitable parking spot and notified the driver about it.

Main Scenario:

1. The function is turned on and off in the settings (in_2).
2. At speeds up to 20 km/ h, the system evaluates the possibility of automatic parallel or perpendicular or parking in an empty space - by the lane markings.
3. The system notifies the driver with a visual signal on the SWP (out_2) about the availability of suitable parking spaces and indicate on SWP (out_1).
4. The driver confirms the intention to park by pressing the button on the SWP (in_2).
5. The system displays the available options for parking on the SWP (out_2). The driver activates the function by selecting a suitable location from the available options on the SWP (in_2) touch screen.
6. The system notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) about the activation of the function, broadcasts the image from the cameras and the planned trajectory of movement on SWP (out_2) and E-mirror (out_4).
7. The car performs steering, controls speed (out_22) and (out_23), switches driving modes (out_9) and notifies other road users about maneuvering using lighting equipment. The function suspends its work when stopped for no more than 10 seconds (TBD).
8. The system turns on the "P" mode (out_9) and notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) and SWP (out_2) and HUD (out_3) about the completion of maneuvering and deactivation of the function and stop indicating on SWP (out_1).


Postconditions:


1. The car is parked.
2. The system notifies the driver with an audible signal about the completion of maneuvering.
3. The function is deactivated.


Alternative Scenarios: 


1. The function is turned on and off in the settings SWP (in_2).
2. At speeds up to 20 km/ h, the system evaluates the possibility of automatic parallel or perpendicular parking in an empty space - by the parked vehicles.
3. The system notifies the driver with a visual signal on the SWP (out_2) about the availability of suitable parking spaces and indicate on SWP (out_1).
4. The driver confirms the intention to park by pressing the button on the SWP (in_2).
5. The system displays the available options for parking on the SWP (out_2). The driver activates the function by selecting a suitable location from the available options on the SWP (in_2) touch screen.
6. The system notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) about the activation of the function, broadcasts the image from the cameras and the planned trajectory of movement on E-mirror (out_4) and change placement by real situation on SWP (out_2) (schematically).
7. The car performs steering, controls speed (out_22) and (out_23), switches driving modes (out_9) and notifies other road users about maneuvering using lighting equipment.
8. The system turns on the "P" mode (out_9) and notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) and SWP (out_2) and HUD (out_3) about the completion of maneuvering and deactivation of the function and stop indicating on SWP (out_1).

Requirements:


1. Manual activation of the function.
2. Manual deactivation of the function.
3. Detection of a suitable parking lot by marking.
4. Detection of a suitable parking lot by the distance between parked vehicles.
5. Notifying the driver about the activation of the function.
6. Notifying the driver about deactivation of the function.
7. Stream of the image from the cameras and the planned trajectory of movement.
8. Automatic taxiing.
9. Automatic speed control.
10. Automatic switching of driving modes.
11. Notifying others road users about maneuvering using lighting equipment.
12. Suspending the function for no more than 10 seconds.
13. Deactivation of the function in the event of intervention by the driver:
a. Braking
b. Accelerating
c. Steering
d. Cancel by SWP
e. Obstacle detection
f. Changing gear mode
g. Opennig door
h. Pull up EPB
i. Unfasten Seatbelt
14. Sound notification of parking sensor operation is possible both out_24 and out_24.1


Restrictions:


1. The system does not work if this car has a trailer.
2. The system does not work when towing a car or other vehicles by car.
3. The system does not work in the presence of a hinged holder.
4. The system operates at speeds not exceeding 20 km/h.
5. The system suspends operation when an obstacle appears on the trajectory of movement.', '[Touchpoint-204408] Touchpoints / 2. SWP Android (Draft)', '[Touchpoint-204407] Touchpoints / 1. SWP RTOS zone (Draft)
