('I-7208', 'PAS Main Scenario', 'Use Case: "PAS Main Scenario"

Preconditions:

Context of use: Description of normal operation of the system when the driver interacts with it.
Goal: compensate insufficient driving skills and reduce maneuvering time
Main character: driver.
Target: parking lot lane marking, vehicle.

1. The car is moving along the road at a speed of up to 20 km/h;
2. The system detected a suitable parking spot and notified the driver about it.

Main Scenario:

1. The function activated searching parking places in the settings on the SWP (in_2).
2. The system evaluates the possibility of automatic parallel or perpendicular or parking in an empty space - by the lane markings.
3. The system notifies the driver with a visual signal on the SWP (out_2) about the availability of suitable parking spaces and indicates on SWP (out_1).
4. The driver confirms the intention to park by pressing the button on the SWP (in_2).
5. The system displays the available options for parking on the SWP (out_2). The driver activates automatic steering wheel rotation the function by selecting a suitable location from the available options on the SWP (in_2) touch screen.
6. The system notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) about the activation of the function, broadcasts the image from the cameras and the planned trajectory of movement on SWP (out_2)).
7. The car helps driver to park and notifies other road users about maneuvering using lighting equipment.
8. The system notifies the driver about which driving mode (in_9) needs to be turned on idicating on SWP (out_2) — the driver controls the speed and switches the driving modes. When stopped for no more than 10 seconds (TBD), the car continues to perform the function.
9. The system turns on the "P" mode (out_9) and notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) and SWP (out_2) and HUD (out_3) about the completion of maneuvering and deactivation of the function and stop indicating on SWP (out_1).


Postconditions:


1. The car is parked.
2. The system notifies the driver with an audible signal about the completion of maneuvering.
3. The function is deactivated.


Alternative Scenarios:


1. The function activated searching parking places in the settings on the SWP (in_2).
2. The system evaluates the possibility of automatic parallel or perpendicular parking in an empty space - by the parked vehicles.
3. The system notifies the driver with a visual signal on the SWP (out_2) about the availability of suitable parking spaces and indicates on SWP (out_1).
4. The driver confirms the intention to park by pressing the button on the SWP (in_2).
5. The system displays the available options for parking on the SWP (out_2). The driver activates automatic steering wheel rotation the function by selecting a suitable location from the available options on the SWP (out_2) touch screen.
6. The system notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) about the activation of the function, broadcasts the image from the cameras and the planned trajectory of movement on SWP (out_2).
7. The car helps driver to park and notifies other road users about maneuvering using lighting equipment.
8. The system notifies the driver about which driving mode needs to be turned on indicating on the SWP (out_2) — the driver controls the speed and switches the driving modes. When stopped for no more than 10 seconds (TBD), the car continues to perform the function.
9. The system turns on the "P" mode (out_9) and notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) and SWP (out_2) and HUD (out_3) about the completion of maneuvering and deactivation of the function and stop indicating on SWP (out_1).


Requirements:


1. Manual activation of the function.
2. Manual deactivation of the function.
3. Detection of a suitable parking lot by marking.
4. Detection of a suitable parking lot by the distance between parked vehicles.
5. Notifying the driver about the activation of the function.
6. Notifying the driver about deactivation of the function.
7. Stream of the image from the cameras and the planned trajectory of movement.
8. Automatic taxiing.
9. Notifying others road users about maneuvering using lighting equipment.
10. Suspending the function for no more than 10 seconds.
11. Deactivation of the function in the event of intervention by the driver:
a. Steering
b. Cancel by SWP
c. Obstacle detection
d. Opennig door
e. Pull up EPB
f. Unfasten Seatbelt
12. Sound notification of parking sensor operation is possible both out_24 and out_24.1.


Restrictions:


1. The system does not work if this car has a trailer.
2. The system does not work when towing a car or other vehicles by car.
3. The system does not work in the presence of a hinged holder.
4. The system operates at speeds not exceeding 20 km/h.
5. The system suspends operation when an obstacle appears on the trajectory of movement.', '[Touchpoint-204408] Touchpoints / 2. SWP Android (Draft)
