('I-25084', 'Configure telemetry data set and frequency of receiving data set (duplicate)', 'Title: Configure telemetry data set and frequency of receiving data set [Release 2.2]


Goal:
To see and configure what data will be included in the required basic and full sets of received telemetry data to have the information carsharing operator need and to ensure optimal operating conditions.


Actors:
User: Fleet owner/manager/operator
System: Atom telematics system
FMS: ATOM-HUB, third party carsharing operator''s FMS


Scope:
Atom telematics system, ATOM-HUB, third party carsharing operator''s FMS, Cloud


Context : 
A B2B user (owner) of a car should be able to set the frequency of recieving frames with data in the telematics settings, select the data he wants to receive in general and in each frame (packet). :
Preconditions: 
The connection parameters are configured, the user can receive telemetry data. The vehicle has an active Internet connection. Trigger: The user navigates to the vehicle/group of vehicles setup service via in_44 ATOM-HUB or third party carsharing operator''s FMS.


Main Scenario: 
1. The FMS gets the current telemetry data set configuration for the vehicle/group of vehicles from Cloud.
2. The FMS configures the list of available basic telemetry data to be received:
for the vehicle turned on with the default period of 1 s for periodic signals and by trigger for state signals. for the vehicle turned off with the default period of 900 s for periodic signals. 3. The user selects/unselects telemetry data from the configured list via in_44 ATOM-HUB or third party carsharing operator''s FMS for the vehicle turned on/off.
4. The user configures groups from selected telemetry signals to receive telemetry data grouped into one telemetry packets/frames via in_44 ATOM-HUB or third party carsharing operator''s FMS.
5. The user specifies the frequency of receiving for each telemetry signal/group of signals within range from 1 s to 65535 s via in_44 ATOM-HUB or third party carsharing operator''s FMS.
6. The user sets up triggers (via in_44 ATOM-HUB or third party carsharing operator''s FMS) to receive each telemetry signal/group of signals specifying one of the following:
By changing the value of one or more signals from the list of available basic telemetry data; By selecting the delta (change threshold) of one or more signals; By reaching a certain value of one or more signals. 7. The user applies the created settings to the vehicle/group of vehicles via in_44 ATOM-HUB or third party carsharing operator''s FMS.


Postconditions: 
Configured sets, triggers, data acquisition schedules are applied to the vehicle/group of vehicles. The user receives telemetry data in accordance with the created sets. Requirements:
For each group of signals the user can set up triggers only based on the the signals included in this group of signals. For each parameter, it should be possible to set one or more transmission types for turned on and turned off vehicle modes. The user must be able to receive telemetry data grouped into telemetry packets/frames, but not each parameter individually. In this case, it should be possible to send data asynchronously in a separate frame. Recording period - the minimum periodicity with which data can be collected (recorded) in the vehicle for sending to the telematics platform. The FMS should allow selection of only telemetry data available for the relevant vehicle states: "Vehicle is turned-on": the state when (or):
The vehicle is booked, In user inspection mode, but with the engine blocked, when the vehicle is rented (standing still or moving). "Vehicle is turned-off": state when the vehicle is parked, closed and not in use (not for rent). In this state the vehicle consumes a minimum of energy, but it has the ability to send required basic telemetry data set, statuses of security systems in case their activation (perimeter violation).', '[Touchpoint-204411] Touchpoints / 44. ATOM-HUB (for B2B) (Decline)', '', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 1160746] Ecosystem product definition /  Configuration tool (Ready for development)', '[FLReq - 1021027] Send general telemetry configuration 发送通用Telemetry配置 / Send general telemetry configuration 发送通用Telemetry配置 (IAT In progress)
