('I-25989', 'Setting upper charge limit session parameter', 'Use-Case Title: Setting upper charge limit session parameter
Goal: to allow the user to set a custom upper charge limit for their Atom''s charging session
Scope: SWP, Smartphone, eMSP, ESC
Actor: user, charging system


Preconditions:
1. The user is authenticated and has access to the eMSP service
2. The eMSP service is available and returns up-to-date data on the location and parameters of the ECS
3. The user is located near the ECS
4. The required connector is free or reserved by the user


Main Scenario:
1. The user connects his electric vehicle to the ECS
2. The user opens the out_5.1 app or out_2SWP and selects the connected ECS
3. The user selects the charging session settings section in_5.1 or in_2
4. The application out_5.1 or out_2displays the charging session settings interface
5. The user configures the upper charge limit (%)
6. After the configuration is complete, the user confirms their selection
7. The application waits for the user to initiate a charging session


Alternative Scenario #7.1:
If the user selects parameters that are unacceptable for this ECS or his vehicle, the system warns of the unacceptability and suggests an adjustment


Alternative Scenario #7.2:
If there is a communication error between the application and the ECS, the user is shown an appropriate notification with a suggestion to try again at a later time


Postconditions:
Charging session parameters are customised according to the user''s preferences', '[Touchpoint-204408] Touchpoints / 2. SWP Android (Draft)
