('I-25995', 'Stop сharging session via SuperApp at Public Charging Stations', 'Use-Case Title: Charging session control (stop) at public charging stations
Goal: the user/driver shall be able to stop the charging session by sent a command to the Atom eMSP service at public charging stations
Scope: Smartphone, Atom eMSP
Actor: user/driver, charging system


Preconditions:
1. The EV is connected to the charging station and the charging session is active
2. The Atom eMSP service is available


Main Scenario:
1. The application displays the details of the charging session with a button to stop the charging session on out_5
2. The user initiates the stopping of the charging session on in_5
3. The application sends a request to stop the charging session to the Atom eMSP service
4. The Atom eMSP service forwards the stop request to the charging station operator.
5. The application displays the information about the completion of the charging session on out_5.

Postconditions:
1. The power supply to the EV is stopped.

Requirements:
1. After the charging session is completed, the application displays a summary to the user based on the data received from the charging station operator. The data include:
Energy consumed (kWh) Total cost Total charging duration If the charging session is only considered complete after the connector is unplugged, the charging cost details will be provided to the user after the connector is disconnected.
2. If the charging session cannot be stopped due to an error, the app notifies the user on out_5', '[Touchpoint - 204414] Touchpoints / 5. Smartphone (Draft)', '[Touchpoint - 204414] Touchpoints / 5. Smartphone (Draft)', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 858064] Ecosystem product definition / Charging Session Management (Ready for development)', ''),
('I-25997', 'Payment for a charging session', 'Use-Case Title: Process payment for a charging session
Goal: to take the payment from a predefined payment method for the charging session
Scope: SWP, Smartphone


Preconditions:
The user is authenticated and has access to the eMSP service The eMSP service is available The payment service is available The driver sends a request to start the charging session via in_2.SWP/in_5.Smartphone Main Scenario:
At the beginning of a charging session, the app shows default payment method and initiates the holding of a certain amount on the default payment method. Once the charging session is complete, the system finalizes the billing process. The remaining balance is returned to the user or the user is additionally charged if necessary. Postconditions:
The charging session was paid successfully and saved to the user profile. Requirements:
The mobile app requires at least one payment method to be available. Alternative Scenario 1.1:
If there is no default payment method the user should be redirected out_2 (via QR code) to Smartphone or notified in smartphone to set the payment method in_5.


Alternative Scenario 1.2:
If the user does not have enough money on the balance, the system offers to choose another payment method or link a new one by redirecting out_2 (via QR code) to Smartphone or notified in smartphone.


Alternative Scenario 1.3:
If the user has any bonuses on his account he can select option "pay with Protons" on charging stations, that support this program. The amount of discount will be defined according to the loyalty program rules. Available only in mobile ([I-32833] Using Protons for Partial Payment of a Charging Session)


Alternative Scenario 1.4:
If the user has the corporate account as a default method we should check the ability of this method for the selected charging station and provide the notification to the user, that the corporate account has been selected or show notification that corporate method is unavailable and redirect out_2 (via QR code).


Alternative Scenario 1.5:
If the user has option of "Free mWt" this method should be set as default automatically and shown via in_2 SWP as a chosen method instead of the card', '[Touchpoint-204408] Touchpoints / 2. SWP Android (Draft)
