Scope: Mobile App


Preconditions:
The application for displaying charging stations on the map layer is launched. The user selected a connector at the charging station. The connector is available for reservation. Triggers:
The user initiates the reservation in_5 of a connector at the charging station. The system initiates the reservation of a connector at the charging station. Main Scenario:
The user selects the reservation time in X minutes in_5. The user confirms the reservation of the connector for the selected time in_5. The system sends a reservation request for the connector to the eMSP service. The system receives a confirmation of the successful reservation of the connector from the eMSP service. Post-conditions:
The connector at the charging station is reserved. Alternative Scenarios A: 
The user initiates the cancellation process on in_5 Post-conditions A:
The reservation has been cancelled successfully and notify the user onout_5 OR
The cancellation unable to proceed due to system failure or connectivity issues, the user is suggest to retry the cancellation after some time on out_5.   
Exceptions:
If eMSP system is not available the user is notified about it out_5. In case of no internet connection, the user is notified about it out_5. If the connector becomes unavailable for reservation at the moment of booking, the user is notified out_5. If the station becomes unavailable during the reservation period, the user is notified out_5. The reservation will be canceled automatically if there are system, server or connecivity issues, or the user does not respond to the confirmation in X seconds.  Requirements:
A countdown timer for the reservation time is displayed to the user. The user has the option to cancel the reservation before it expires. The user can adjust the reservation time from 5 to 30 minutes in 5-minute increments. If the reservation is paid, the user sees the final cost when changing the reservation time. When the reservation time expires, the reservation is automatically finalized.', '[Touchpoint - 204414] Touchpoints / 5. Smartphone (Draft)
