('I-31031', 'Use Case: B2C Client Registration', 'Use Case: B2C Client Registration 
Objective:
To enable secure, seamless, and user-friendly registration for B2C clients via web, mobile web (mweb), Atom HUB, or SuperApp platforms, offering both simple and complete registration options with enhanced security and usability features.
Actors:
New client Atom system Preconditions:
The client has internet access and a mobile phone. The website or application is accessible and operational. Scope:
The scope of the B2C Client Registration includes the following key components designed to ensure a secure, seamless, and user-centric registration experience via web, mobile web (mweb), Atom HUB, or SuperApp platforms. The registration supports both simple and comprehensive processes.
Platform Accessibility:  Ensure the registration process is accessible on web, mobile web, Atom HUB, and SuperApp platforms, supporting a wide range of devices and browsers.   User Authentication:  Implement authentication using phone numbers and OTP, with enhanced security via optional secondary verification methods (e.g., email verification, biometric authentication).   Data Entry and Validation:  Provide a comprehensive registration form with fields such as First Name, Last Name, email, and date of birth. Implement real-time data validation to ensure accuracy and completeness, including email format checks.   Security Measures:  Utilize secure protocols (HTTPS) and encryption for data transmission and storage. Incorporate additional security layers beyond OTP for heightened protection.   User Guidance and Support:  Include contextual help, tooltips, or guides to facilitate the registration process. Offer live support or a helpdesk option during registration for immediate assistance.   Feedback and Consent:  Collect user consent for data usage and privacy policies through clear disclosures. Enable an optional feedback mechanism post-registration to gather insights on the user experience.   Confirmation and Onboarding:  Provide instant confirmation of successful registration, along with onboarding information. Redirect users to a welcome page or their original entry platform, depending on preferences.   Scalability and Performance:  Design a system that accommodates high volumes of registrations with reliable performance, supported by scalable infrastructure.   Continuous Improvement:  Regularly review registration analytics to identify areas for optimization. Implement a feedback loop for ongoing enhancements based on user experiences and technological advancements.   Administration and Control:  Allow administrators to configure field requirements and form display settings to align with changing business needs and regulations.   Postconditions:
The user has an Atom ID linked to their verified data. The user receives a confirmation email with next steps and support contact details. Notes:
Admin-controlled settings can adjust field requirements and registration form display. The system supports scenarios for "simple registration (mobile number + OTP)" and "complete registration," adaptable to internal Atom settings. Continuous Improvement:
Feedback collection and analysis for process enhancement. Regular updates and audits for security purposed, maintaining compliance with the latest standards.', '[Touchpoint - 204414] Touchpoints / 5. Smartphone (Draft)', '[Touchpoint - 204414] Touchpoints / 5. Smartphone (Draft)', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 881393] Ecosystem product definition / B2C user registration and authentification (Ready for development)', ''),
