('I-31142', 'Receive a set of telemetry data from the vehicle turned on (B2B) [Release 2.2]', 'Title: 
Receive a set of telemetry data from the vehicle turned on (B2B) (Release 2.2)


Goal:
FMS User/ATOM HUB User obtains the telemetry data available when the vehicle is turn on to analyze the status of the vehicle, and how well the user controls it.


Scope:
ATOM-HUB, third party carsharing operator''s FMS, Atom telematics system.
Context:
The vehicle systems in turned-on state (see requirements) are running and their current status can be sent as part of telemetry data. When entering this state, the carsharing operator must receive all current data about the state of the vehicle and its systems. In this state, data with a possible high frequency of sending is sent when it changes.


Actors:
User: Fleet owner/manager/operator
Human: Driver
System: Atom telematics system


Preconditions: 
The connection parameters are configured, the user can receive telemetry data. The list and rules for receiving telemetry data are configured. Triggers (AND):
A driver opens a vehicle through the carsharing operator''s application. The vehicle systems turn on. Main Scenario: 
Atom telematics system collects and aggregates the data from systems, sensors in accordance with the established set or Regular Data Set. Atom telematics system sends the collected and aggregated data to the carsharing operator a given frequency. The user regularly receives a complete set of data and analyzes it through the third party carsharing operator''s FMS or out_44 ATOM-HUB. Alternative Scenario: 
2a. If the car is outside the network coverage area, the data is saved to the on-board storage medium.
When the vehicle is within the network coverage the Atom telematics system sends the data from the on-board carrier to the carsharing operator. Postconditions: 
The vehicle sends data according to the specified frequency. The user has analyzed the status of the vehicle, and how well the user controls it. Restrictions: 
By default, the regular data set is sent every 5 minutes. The established data set shall consist of values from regular data set wich are actually changed on the vehicle. The established data set shall be sent to the carsharing operator no more often than with the max raster. Data storage capacity is at least 72 hours but no more than a week. Requirements:
"Vehicle is turned-on": the state when (or):
