('I-31437', 'Receiving telemetry data on a trigger [Release 2.2]', 'Title: Receiving telemetry data on a trigger [Release 2.2]


Goal :
Fleet owner/manager/operator obtains the information about the status of vehicle elements and analyze the changes on time to prevent premature wear of parts and ensure optimal operating conditions.


Scope:
Atom telematics system, Integration with third party FMS, Cloud, Data Platform, Fleet API


Actors :
User: Fleet owner/manager/operator
System: Atom telematics system, third party carsharing operator''s FMS


Preconditions: 
The connection parameters are configured, the Fleet owner/manager/operator can receive telemetry data. Triggers have been configured to receive data when the specific events occur . Trigger: An event has occurred for which a trigger is set.
Postconditions: 
Fleet owner/manager/operator analyzes the data from the List of Telemetry data on a trigger via out_82 third party FMS. Exception (If the vehicle is outside the network coverage area):
