('I-32193', 'Remotely request a telemetry data from the vehicle turned on (B2B)', 'Title: Remotely request a telemetry data from the vehicle turned on (B2B)


Goal: Obtain the telemetry data by request when the vehicle is turn on to analyze the status of the vehicle.


Scope: Atom telematics system, third party carsharing operator''s FMS.
Context: Atom driver has problems operating the vehicle. It''s necessary for Fleet owner/manager/operator to request the current telemetry data when solving the problem. In this case, waiting for the telemetry update at a set frequency (for example 30 s) is not an effective solution.


Actors:
Human actor: Fleet owner/manager/operator
System actor: Atom telematics system


Preconditions: 
The connection parameters are configured. The list and rules for receiving telemetry data are configured. Atom vehicle is turned on. Triggers: Fleet owner/manager/operator sends a request to get a carrent telemetry data from the vehicle via in_82 third party FMS.


Main Scenario: 
The system collects and aggregates telemetry data configured from available data set for Atom vehicle turned on and telemetry data on a trigger. The system sends the requested data to Fleet owner/manager/operator. Fleet owner/manager/operator receives a requested data and analyzes it via out_82 third party FMS. Alternative Scenario (If the vehicle has lost its internet connection):
3a. The system saves the data to the on-board storage medium.
4a. When the vehicle is within the network coverage the system sends the data from the on-board carrier to Fleet owner/manager/operator.


Postconditions: 
Fleet owner/manager/operator analyzed the status of the vehicle. Requirements:
The data received from the vehicle must be time-stamped when it is received in the vehicle. Fleet owner/manager/operator must be able to receive telemetry data grouped into telemetry packets/frames, but not each parameter individually. In this case, it should be possible to send data asynchronously in a separate frame. The depth of archival storage of vehicle data in cloud must be at least 24 months. "Vehicle is turned-on": Vehicle State is set Invisible awake or Standby or Drive. From Carsharing driver''s point view: the state when (or):
The vehicle is booked, In user inspection mode, but with the engine blocked, when the vehicle is rented (standing still or moving).', '[Touchpoint-978170] Touchpoints / 82. third party FMS (Draft)', '[Touchpoint-978170] Touchpoints / 82. third party FMS (Draft)', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 1160747] Ecosystem product definition / Seamless connectivity (Ready for development)', ''),
