('I-32365', 'PAS Main Scenario', 'Use Case: "PAS Main Scenario"

Preconditions:

Context of use: Description of normal operation of the system when the driver interacts with it.
Goal: compensate insufficient driving skills and reduce maneuvering time
Main character: driver.
Target: parking lot lane marking, vehicle.


1. The system is turned on;
2. The car is moving along the road at a speed of up to 20 km/h;
3. The system detected a suitable parking spot and notified the driver about it.

Main Scenario:

1. The function activated searching parking places on the SWP (in_2).
2. The system evaluates the possibility of automatic parallel or perpendicular parking or parking in an empty space.
3. The system notifies the driver with a visual signal on the SWP (out_2) about the availability of suitable parking spaces and indicates on SWP (out_1).
4. The driver activates the function by selecting a suitable parking spot from the available options on the SWP (in_2) touch screen with description that PAS will be used.
5. The system notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) about the activation of the function, broadcasts the image from the cameras on SWP (out_2) and E-mirror (out_4).
6. The car performs steering and notifies the driver about which driving mode (in_9) needs to be turned on idicating on SWP (out_2) and E-mirror (out_4) — the driver controls the speed and switches the driving modes. When stopped for no more than 10 seconds, the car continues to perform the function.  
7. The driver turns on the "P" mode (out_9).
8. System notifies the driver with an audible signal (out_24.1) and SWP (out_2) and HUD (out_3) about the completion of maneuvering and deactivation of the function and stop indicating on SWP (out_1).


Postconditions:


1. The car is parked.
2. The system notifies the driver with an audible signal about the completion of maneuvering.
3. The function is deactivated.




Requirements:


1. Manual activation of the function.
2. Manual deactivation of the function.
3. Detection of a suitable parking spot.
5. Notifying the driver about the activation of the function.
6. Notifying the driver about deactivation of the function.
7. Stream of the image from the cameras 
8. Automatic taxiing.
9. Suspending the function for movement stops no more than 10 seconds.
10. Deactivation of the function in the event of intervention by the driver:
a. Steering
b. Cancel by SWP
c. Obstacle detection with stops moving more than 10 seconds.
d. Opennig door
e. Pull up EPB
f. Unfasten Seatbelt
g. driver not use notifications about actions for more than 10 seconds
h. driver perform NOT notified action
11. Sound notification of parking sensor operation is possible out_24.1.
12. Notifying others road users about maneuvering using lighting equipment, hazard lights.


Restrictions:


1. The system operates at speeds not exceeding 20 km/h.
2. The function stops working than car stops moving more than 10 seconds', '[Touchpoint-204408] Touchpoints / 2. SWP Android (Draft)
