('I-32441', 'Displaying a speed limit on the current route section', 'Use-Case Title:
Displaying a speed limit on the current route section


Goal:
In real-time tracking of speed limits on the current route section to avoid speed exceeding.


Context:
The navigation system receives information about the speed limit on the current route section and displays it via out_2 SWP Android and out_3 HUD. When the vehicle is moving along the public road and ACC/DA, TSR functions are activated the navigation system displays the speed limit value from TSR system in case of contradiction between the information on the speed limit from TSR system and the speed limit values on the maps.


Scope:
Navigation system HUD System IVI General Content System Geolocation ADAS Actors:
User: driver
Precondition:
The ACC/DA and TSR functions are activated. The navigation system is connected and working correctly. The TSR system correctly recognizes speed limit signs. Trigger:
A vehicle enters a section of road with a changed speed limit. Main scenario:
The navigation system receives information about the speed limit for the current section of the route. The TSR system recognizes the speed limit sign and transmits the information to the navigation system. The navigation system compares the speed limit information from the TSR system with the data on the maps. In the event of a contradiction between the data, the navigation system selects a value from the TSR system. The navigation system displays the current speed limit value on out_2 SWP Android and out_3 HUD. The driver sees the current speed limit value and adjusts the speed of the vehicle if necessary. Postcondition:
The current speed limit value is displayed on the SWP Android out_2 and out_3 HUD. The driver has up-to-date information about the speed limit and can avoid speeding. The navigation system continues to monitor changes in the speed limit on the route.', '', '[Touchpoint-204408] Touchpoints / 2. SWP Android (Draft)
