('I-32944', 'Remote control the vehicle through its telematics platform', 'Title:
Remote control the vehicle through its telematics platform (B2B)


Goal:
To provide carsharing services and create new user experiences.


Scope:
Atom telematics system, vehicle system


Actors:
User: Fleet owner/manager/operator
System: vehicle systems


Preconditions:
The vehicle''s telematics are operational and configured. Triggers: Fleet owner/manager/operator sends a control command from the available list via in_82 third party FMS.


Main scenario:
The Atom telematics system receives a control command. The corresponding vehicle system changes its operating mode/state and status according to the control command. The Atom telematics system sends information to Fleet owner/manager/operator that the command has been completed and the current status of the system. Fleet owner/manager/operator receives a notification about the execution of the command and the current status via out_82 third party FMS. Exceptions:
2a. If the command is incorrect or the vehicle system cannot execute it, the Atom telematics system sends a message that the command cannot be executed and the reason.
Fleet owner/manager/operator receives a response from the vehicle and analyzes it via out_82 third party FMS. Requirements:
The communication channel from the telematics platform of the carsharing operator to the vehicle should be protected and isolated from the outside world as much as possible. Fleet owner/manager/operator must be able to send simple and combined remote control commands. When using combined commands, he should be able to control and ensure that the command is fully executed.          № Remote Command   1  Turn on/off climate control. There should be a possibility of remote car heating
