('I-33157', 'Start scheduled update', 'Goal
To start the vehicle’s flashing automatically at scheduled times without user approval.


Context
Schedules are managed by external systems via the OTA Cloud API, after creation it stays a read-only replica on TBOX for offline execution. When a scheduled run starts, approval notifications must not be shown. Results are observable via “View logs” / “View campaign results.” / API interaction


Scope
OTA Vehicle; OTA Cloud; Actors
User (Human actors):
(none) Systems (System actors):
External System OTA Cloud OTA Vehicle Preconditions
The vehicle is not under flashing process. Schedule exists in OTA Cloud and its stored copy on TBOX. Triggers
The scheduled date and time arrive. Main Scenario
OTA Vehicle detects that a stored schedule date and time has arrived. OTA Vehicle starts the precondition-checking process. OTA Vehicle starts flashing process. OTA Cloud records logs. TBOX saves the schedule for future executions. 

Alternative scenario
Precondition checking process failed
3a1. OTA Vehicle evaluates preconditions and detects unmet items (e.g., doors open, ignition state).
3a2. OTA Vehicle informs the Approver on SWP with corrective guidance or informs by API.
3a3. Approver corrects conditions (e.g., exits vehicle, closes doors, charges battery).
Rejoins step 3.
OR
3b3. Approver cannot correct conditions (e.g., exits vehicle, closes doors, charges battery).
End of process.




Flashing successfully fails
4a1. OTA Vehicle detects a flashing error and halts the update (error code recorded).
4a2. OTA Vehicle performs safe recovery/rollback per policy and logs the failure to OTA Cloud.
4a3. OTA Vehicle completes flashing unsuccessfully.
Rejoins step 5 (Records logs).


Flashing unsuccessfully fails
4a1. OTA Vehicle detects a flashing error (error code recorded).
4a2. OTA Vehicle cannot perform recovery/rollback and shows the error message to the user (SWP / API).
4a3. OTA Vehicle completes flashing unsuccessfully.
End of process.


Post Conditions
The car is flashed without user approval. The schedule remains stored for future occurrences. Events are auditable and visible via API for logs/results also throuth notification. Requirements
TBOX stores a read-only replica. TBOX shall start the preconditions checking process without the internet connection. The stored schedule shall persist after precondition checks and after flashing, and be reused for subsequent campaigns on the vehicle. Approval notifications shall not be shown when the check is started by schedule.', '', '', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 1165100] Ecosystem product definition / Approval & Scheduling Control (Ready for development)', '[FLReq - 1377976] OTA Master / Set/Cancel OTA Update Schedule (New)
