A model includes basic identity (brand/series/model/year, VIN template, company), its ECU set, upgrade strategy, and the conditions.This use case covers creation/modification.
Scope:
CMS; Actors
User (Human actors):    Campaign owner   Systems (System actors):    CMS   Preconditions:
The user is authenticated. Triggers:
A new vehicle model was released, or modifications were introduced to an existing model. Main Scenario:
Campaign owner creates the new vehicle model. System presents the Basic Information form. Campaign owner fills the Basic Information form. System validates required fields. System saves the model in CMS. Campaign owner configures the ECU List: associates ECUs from the catalog or imports inspection parameters. System validates ECU associations and saves them. Campaign owner defines Upgrade steps: orders the pipeline across ECUs, and saves the strategy. Campaign owner configures Preconditions: selects required conditions (e.g., speed=0, gear=P). Campaign owner configures Pre-conditions for entering OTA: toggles gating options (e.g., OTA mode, update reminder). System saves the changes. Post Conditions:
A vehicle-model configuration is saved and stored in CMS. The model is available for campaign targeting and update execution rules. Alter Scenario:
1a. Edit existing model instead of creating new:
1a1. Campaign owner opens the model from the list using Edit.
1a2. System loads the current configuration; steps 6–12 are performed to adjust ECU list, strategy, and preconditions.
Rejoins step 11.


8a. Auto-generate strategy:
8a1. Campaign owner selects automatic configuration to generate a default pipeline.
8a2. Campaign owner adjusts steps if needed and saves.
Rejoins step 9.


Requirements:
The system shall validate and persist Basic Information (brand, series, model, model year, VIN template, owner company, PKI strategy/supplier). The system shall require Brand, Series, Model, Model Year, Owner Company as mandatory fields on creation. The system shall accept the VIN template as optional and shall validate it against the standard 17-character VIN pattern when provided The system shall allow associating ECUs. The system shall manage an API to create vehicle models and update.', '', '', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 1163886] Ecosystem product definition / Campaign Management (Ready for development)', '[FLReq - 1489098] Vehicle Info Management / Vehicle Model Management (New)
