('I-33979', 'Charging Notifications', 'Goal
Inform the user about charging session progress, reservation updates, and payment outcomes in a timely way without requiring the user to open the app.


Context
Unified notification delivery for charging-related events across the eMSP experience, including session lifecycle (start, progress, completion, interruption, errors), reservation lifecycle (created, confirmed, reminder, expiration, cancellation), and payment events (success, failure, refunds). Notifications are delivered through configured channels (push/SMS) and support user awareness and decision-making during charging


Actors
Car User


Assumptions and Limitations
Notifications are delivered via push and/or SMS based on user preferences and platform permissions
Only meaningful events trigger notifications; low-signal updates may be suppressed
Sensitive payment details are not exposed in notification content
Delivery depends on network connectivity and third-party messaging reliability
Critical system or safety-related notifications may not be fully disabled by the user', '', '', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 1379485] Ecosystem product definition / Notification Service (Ready for development)', ''),
('I-33980', 'Service Billing', 'Goal
Calculate and generate charges for paid ecosystem services based on predefined monetization rules


Context
Automatic billing triggered by service usage or subscription events, producing chargeable amounts for further payment processing across ecosystem products


Actors
System
Car User


Assumptions and Limitations
Billing is rule-based and predefined
No user interaction is required
Payment execution is handled by external payment services', '', '', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 1165144] Ecosystem product definition / Monetezation (Ready for development)', ''),
('I-33981', 'Payment API', 'Goal
Provide a unified and secure interface for initiating, processing, and tracking payment transactions across ecosystem services


Context
Backend API used by ecosystem products and services to execute payments based on calculated charges, ensuring standardized interaction with external payment providers


Actors
System
External Payment Provider


Assumptions and Limitations
API is invoked only by trusted internal services
All payment requests are validated before processing
Payment authorization and settlement are handled by external payment providers', '', '', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 1165171] Ecosystem product definition / Payment API (Ready for development)', ''),
