('I-34004', 'Use Case: Process OCPI Charging Session Data', 'Title: Process OCPI Charging Session Data
Goal: Receive, validate, and process real-time session updates and final Charge Detail Records (CDRs) from CPO partners via OCPI protocol.
Context: To ensure accurate billing and user transparency during roaming, the eMSP system must handle standardized messages from CPO. This involves receiving real-time status (Session object) while charging is active and a final, signed data package (CDR) containing meter values and costs immediately after the session ends, compliant with OCPI v2.2.1+ standards.', '', '', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 1248445] Ecosystem product definition / Integration with Operators (OCPI) (Ready for development)', ''),
('I-34005', 'Find Charging Station on Web Map', 'Title: Find Charging Station on Web Map


Goal: Allow users to locate compatible charging stations and view their details directly on the website map without installing the app.


Context: Potential and current users visit the website to check coverage or plan a route. The web interface displays a map with all aggregated partner stations (via roaming), allowing users to click on a point and see essential details like connector types, power (kW), price, and current status, demonstrating the service''s value proposition.', '', '', '[ECOSYSTEM.PD_Soft - 1248447] Ecosystem product definition / Charging WebSite (Ready for development)', '')
